{
	"name": "Absorb Flesh",
	"type": "feat",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p>The [[lookup @name lowercase]] touches one other malakai or an intact corpse, absorbing either extraneous flesh from a fellow drone or taking what it needs from the corpse.</p><br><p>The [[lookup @name lowercase]] regains 10 hit points. If the target was another malakai, that malakai loses 10 hit points. If the target was a corpse, part of the corpse is destroyed.</p><br><p>A tiny creature can only be absorbed once. A small or medium creature can be absorbed twice, a large creature four times, a huge creature eight times, and a gargantuan creature 16 times.</p><br><p>The [[lookup @name lowercase]] can more efficiently absorb corpses if they take a minute for each absorption. In that case, they get 20 hit points each time they use this ability.</p><br><p>Once the corpse has been absorbed once, it is no longer intact for the purposes of Revivify or Raise Dead.</p>",
